AI Based Study Planner System

1. Introduction

In today’s fast-paced academic environment, students often struggle to manage their study time efficiently. This project presents a Study Planner System that helps users track, analyze, and improve their study habits using Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) concepts.

The system is a command-line Python application that allows users to store study data, visualize it, and receive intelligent suggestions.

2. Objectives

The main objectives of this project are:

To track daily study hours
To analyze subject-wise performance
To visualize study patterns using graphs
To predict future study behavior using ML
To provide AI-based recommendations


3. Technologies Used

Programming Language: Python
Libraries Used:
matplotlib → for graph visualization
tkinter → for GUI timer
numpy → for numerical operations
sklearn (LinearRegression) → for ML prediction
File Handling: Text file (study.txt)
4. System Description

The system works using a simple menu-driven interface. All study data is stored in a file named study.txt, ensuring persistence.

5. Features of the System

5.1 Add Study Data

User enters subject and study hours
Data is saved in file

5.2 View Data

Displays all study records
Calculates total study hours
5.3 Study Timer (GUI)

Timer built using tkinter
Automatically saves study time after completion

5.4 Graph Visualization

Bar chart of subjects vs hours
Helps in visual understanding

5.5 Machine Learning Prediction

Uses Linear Regression
Predicts next day study hours
If ML library unavailable → uses average method

5.6 AI Recommendation System

Suggests:

Increase study time (for weak subjects)
Maintain performance (for strong subjects)

5.7 Performance Analysis

Identifies:
Weakest subject
Strongest subject

6. Working Principle

User inputs study data
Data is stored in study.txt
System reads data for:
Graph generation
Analysis
Prediction
ML model analyzes past trends
AI logic provides recommendations

7. Algorithm Overview

Prediction Algorithm
Input: Past study hours
Process:
Convert data into numerical format
Train Linear Regression model
Predict next value
Output: Future study hours
Recommendation Algorithm
Calculate average study time
Compare each subject:
Below average → Increase time
Above average → Good

8. Advantages

Simple and easy to use
Helps improve time management
Provides intelligent insights
Works without internet
Combines AI + ML concepts

9. Limitations

Uses basic ML model (Linear Regression)
Limited UI (mostly command-line)
No cloud storage
Prediction accuracy depends on data

10. Future Enhancements

Add mobile or web application
Use advanced ML models
Add reminders and notifications
